@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Improve clipping for scrollable containers so offscreen children cannot draw outside the parent content rect.

Goals:
- Add clipping bounds to drawing operations.
- Ensure children of scrollable sprites are clipped to the sprite content rect.
- Preserve absolute sprite behavior unless explicitly affected by clipping.
- Keep clipping implementation minimal and internal to `ConvoTuiCtrl`.

Acceptance criteria:
- Scrolled children do not draw above, below, left, or right of the parent content rect.
- Borders remain visible and are not overwritten by clipped children.
- Nested scrollable containers clip correctly.
- Inline text clipping continues to work.
- Non-scrollable layouts render as before.

